<article id="post-62" class="post-62 page type-page status-publish hentry">
		<div class="entry-content clearfix">
		<p>Welcome to the <strong>Neural Engineering Vision Laboratory (NEVL)</strong>. We apply the tools and techniques of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neural_engineering">neural engineering</a> to problems in ophthalmology and vision science. Our group is primarilyÂ interested in developing new tools for research, diagnosis, and treatment of retinal diseases, including glaucoma, macular degeneration, retinitis pigmentosa, diabetic retinopathy and retinal ischemia. The methods we use include electrophysiology, modeling, instrumentation design and microfabrication. We collaborate with several laboratories including those in other departments at UIC, other Chicago institutions and universities across the country.</p>
			</div>
	<footer class="entry-meta-bar clearfix">
		<div class="entry-meta clearfix">
